C%20American%20firms%20are%20also%20becoming%20less%20willing%20to%20go%20to%20bat%20for%20China%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reinforce%20the%20idea%20that%20China's%20market%20is%20crucial%20to%20the%20success%20of%20their%20futures.%20Beijing%20is%20finding%20itself%20increasingly%20friendless%20in%20Washington%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20weight%20of%20the%20US-China%20relationship%20is%20shifting%20from%20constructing%20mutually%20beneficial%20economic%20ties%20to%20balancing%20antagonistic%20national%20security%20interests.%20Rather%20than%20try%20to%20resurrect%20the%20Chinese%20consumer%20and%2C%20by%20extension%2C%20reestablish%20critical%20economic%20ties%20with%20America%2C%20though%2C%20its%20leader%2C%20Xi%20Jinping%2C%20doesn't%20seem%20to%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BXi%20doesn't%20wake%20up%20every%20day%2C%20look%20at%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20panic%2C%26quot%3B%20Lee%20Miller%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20survey%20firm%20China%20Beige%20Book%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BHe%20thinks%20they're%20doing%20what%20they%20need%20to%20do%2C%20and%20it's%20painful%20medicine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20China%20needs%20to%20do%2C%20in%20Xi's%20mind%2C%20is%20make%20itself%20indestructible%20and%20indispensable.%20That%20means%20supporting%20state-owned%20enterprises%20and%20other%20domestic%20firms%2C%20giving%20them%20a%20leg%20up%20in%20the%20market%20as%20they%20compete%20against%20foreign%20firms%20for%20a%20piece%20of%20China's%20shrinking%20economic%20pie.%20It%20means%20getting%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20addicted%20to%20China's%20products%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20cheap%20manufactured%20goods%20but%20also%20advanced%20technology%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jiinping-future-tech-global-economy-semiconductors-military-failing-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemiconductors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-crushing-us-america-battle-energy-evs-batteries-tech-war-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebatteries%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-ai-wreak-havoc-america-world-economy-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20commodities%20that%20make%20up%20the%20downstream%20of%20its%20supply%20chain%2C%20such%20as%20gallium%20and%20germanium.%20Self-sufficiency%20for%20me%2C%20but%20not%20for%20thee.%20It%20is%20a%20strategy%20so%20imbalanced%20that%20it%20dares%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it.%20And%20it%20does%20not%20include%20Chinese%20people%20getting%20hooked%20on%20frappuccinos%20made%20by%20an%20American%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20peace%20between%20China%20and%20the%20US%20has%20been%20the%20notion%20that%20we%20can%20do%20business%20with%20one%20another%20even%20though%20we%20don't%20share%20the%20same%20values.%20The%20US%20strives%20to%20be%20an%20open%20society%3B%20China%20is%20increasingly%20closed.%20We%20may%20butt%20heads%20in%20the%20South%20China%20Sea%2C%20over%20Taiwan%2C%20over%20resources%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20but%20it%20was%20money%20that%20kept%20us%20together.%20Without%20access%20to%20the%20Chinese%20consumer%2C%20US%20stakeholders%20have%20less%20reason%20to%20see%20China%20as%20a%20market%20and%20more%20reason%20to%20see%20it%20as%20a%20menace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20demand%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20pandemic%20lockdowns%20ended%20in%202023%2C%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20experienced%20what%20is%20known%20on%20Wall%20Street%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdead%20cat%20bounce.%26quot%3B%20Picture%20a%20dead%20cat%20being%20dropped%3A%20It%20may%20rebound%20off%20the%20ground%20a%20bit%2C%20but%20after%20that%2C%20it's%20going%20nowhere.%20Similarly%2C%20China's%20decimated%20economy%20got%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20pickup%20once%20COVID%20restrictions%20ended%20in%202023%2C%20but%20a%20year%20later%2C%20things%20look%20bleak.%20Beijing's%205%25%20GDP%20growth%20target%20%E2%80%94%20once%20seen%20as%20a%20slam%20dunk%20%E2%80%94%20is%20now%20openly%20in%20doubt.%20Debt%20in%20the%20property%20market%20is%20still%20dragging%20the%20economy%20down%2C%20and%20the%20government's%20bets%20on%20an%20export%20boom%20don't%20seem%20to%20be%20paying%20off.%20Prolonged%20deflation%20erodes%20the%20value%20of%20China's%20currency%20and%20ultimately%20means%20it%20has%20to%20sell%20more%20exports%20to%20make%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20money.%20Unemployment%20for%20Chinese%20young%20people%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2016%20and%2024%20spiked%20to%2017.1%25%20in%20July%2C%20forcing%20a%20new%20class%20of%20(often)%20overeducated%20graduates%20to%20compete%20for%20low-wage%20jobs.%20They're%20being%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Frotten-tail-kids-chinas-rising-youth-unemployment-breeds-new-working-class-2024-08-21%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Brotten%20tail%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20Brutal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20previous%20downturns%2C%20the%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20reacted%20by%20shooting%20the%20money%20gun%20%E2%80%94%20spending%20on%20infrastructure%2C%20housing%2C%20and%20keeping%20people%20employed.%20This%20kept%20the%20wheels%20turning%2C%20but%20each%20turn%20left%20the%20country%20with%20a%20larger%20pile%20of%20debt.%20There%20is%20only%20one%20way%20to%20get%20off%20a%20ride%20like%20this%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20painful%20period%20of%20paying%20down%20debt%20that%20can%20obliterate%20demand%20in%20an%20economy.%20Xi%20has%20decided%20to%20put%20down%20the%20money%20gun%20without%20doing%20anything%20to%20aid%20average%20Chinese%20households%20as%20the%20economy%20shrinks.%20Xi%20told%20party%20members%20in%20July%20to%20show%20%26quot%3Bunwavering%20faith%26quot%3B%20in%20his%20grand%20economic%20strategy%2C%20but%20he%20has%20paid%20them%20in%20dust.%20Earlier%20this%20month%2C%20in%20an%20unusual%20divergence%20from%20Xi's%20policy%2C%20the%20former%20head%20of%20the%20People's%20Bank%20of%20China%2C%20Yi%20Gang%2C%20said%20that%20the%20government%20should%20engage%20in%20some%20kind%20of%20stimulus%20to%20reach%20its%20already-softened%20growth%20targets.%20The%20inflation%20that%20does%20exist%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20as%20the%20Carnegie%20Endowment%20fellow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fmichaelxpettis%2Fstatus%2F1833022599712113044c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichael%20Pettis%20noted%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20being%20driven%20by%20higher%20food%20prices%20due%20to%20shortages%20%E2%80%94%20hardly%20a%20sign%20that%20things%20could%20be%20turning%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%20companies%20have%20been%20feeling%20this%20burn.%20At%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20year%2C%20China's%20Apple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-new-iphone-16-china-market-sales-glowtime-2024-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520downward%2520trend%2520has%2520continued%2Cdrop%2520in%2520the%2520second%2520quarter.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EiPhone%20sales%20fell%2024%25%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they've%20been%20trending%20down%20ever%20since.%20Starbucks%2C%20which%20has%20more%20than%207%2C300%20stores%20in%20China%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-starbucks-is-struggling-in-china-sales-prices-competition-coffee-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaw%20comparable%20store%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20revenue%20generated%20by%20a%20retail%20location%20relative%20to%20its%20performance%20in%20the%20past%20%E2%80%94%20fall%2014%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnikes-sales-to-fall-this-year-as-turnaround-plan-continues-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENike's%20China%20woes%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20contributed%20to%20its%20year-to-date%20nearly%2030%25%20stock%20slump.%20F%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinside