na-market-sales-glowtime-2024-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520downward%2520trend%2520has%2520continued%2Cdrop%2520in%2520the%2520second%2520quarter.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esales%20surging%2070%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20the%20year.%20Starbucks%20opened%20its%20first%20China%20store%20in%201999%20and%20used%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.joebm.com%2Fvol9%2F649-DM1003.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatus%20symbol%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20now%20it%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fbusiness%2Fcompanies%2Farticle%2F3273882%2Fstarbucks-feels-chill-china-prices-vibes-lose-favour-thrifty-coffee-fans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estiffer%20competition%20from%20Chinese%20brands%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20Luckin%20and%20Cotti%20Coffee.%20This%20is%20no%20accident%3B%20it's%20part%20of%20Xi's%20plan%20to%20rid%20China%20of%20foreign%20dependence%20and%20influence.%20In%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uschina.org%2Freports%2F2024-member-survey%3Futm_campaign%3DMarketing_Cloud%26utm_medium%3Demail%26utm_source%3DNews%2BRelease%2B2024%2BMember%2BSurvey%26%2520utm_content%3Dhttps%253a%252f%252fwww.uschina.org%252freports%252f2024-member-survey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS-China%20Business%20Council%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2080%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20that%20%26quot%3BChina's%20industrial%20policies%20are%20strengthening%20companies%20that%20were%20previously%20uncompetitive%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20competition%20from%20Chinese%20rivals%20came%20in%20as%20the%20third-highest%20concern%20about%20doing%20business%20there.%20Yes%2C%20US%20companies%20are%20still%20making%20money%20in%20China.%20But%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fchina-has-found-another-way-to-hurt-usa-inc-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20uncomfortable%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Magic%208%20Ball%20says%20the%20outlook%20is%20not%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EYa%20gotta%20have%20friends%20(in%20Washington)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20elite%20financial%20firms%20will%20still%20publicly%20tell%20you%20they%20expect%20to%20keep%20investing%20in%20China%20even%20though%20the%20investment-banking%20business%20in%20the%20country%20has%2C%20as%20JPMorgan%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%20recently%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F25d17ea1-17e8-4f6a-9da4-9f726970d4e4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bfallen%20off%20a%20cliff%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Behind%20closed%20doors%2C%20however%2C%20Wall%20Street%20power%20players%20are%20singing%20a%20much%20different%20tune.%20It's%20not%20just%20the%20pressure%20from%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20also%20the%20political%20climate.%20It's%20hard%20to%20do%20business%20in%20a%20country%20where%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jinping-hiding-bad-data-economy-debt-real-estate-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edata%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fmissing-chinese-ceo-stock-plunge-cooperate-government-probe-china-renaissance-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%3C%2Fa%3E%20keep%20disappearing.%20Wall%20Street's%20change%20of%20attitude%20is%20reflected%20in%20the%20flow%20of%20money%20into%20China%3A%20Foreign%20direct%20investment%20is%20at%20a%2030-year%20low%2C%20and%20from%20June%20to%20(as%20best%20we%20can%20tell)%20early%20August%2C%20investors%20pulled%20%2412%20billion%20from%20China's%20stock%20market.%20This%20could%20make%202024%20China's%20first%20year%20of%20equity%20outflows.%20But%20we%20won't%20know%20for%20sure%20because%2C%20given%20the%20equity%20dumping%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F6e7a4129-d365-4905-8d9b-cc3f5ada5187%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChina%20decided%20last%20month%20to%20stop%20publishing%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20showing%20net%20investment%20flows%20from%20foreign%20funds%20into%20mainland%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20declining%20Sino-Wall%20Street%20links%20are%20of%20particular%20note%2C%20not%20because%20I%20think%20the%20people%20of%20Shanghai%20and%20Beijing%20will%20miss%20drinking%20Moutai%20with%20Goldman%20Sachs%20bankers%20but%20because%20Wall%20Street%20is%20a%20powerful%20ally%20in%20Washington.%20They%20arrange%20meetings%20between%20stakeholders%20and%20talk%20up%20the%20benefits%20of%20the%20cross-Pacific%20relationship.%20Once%20upon%20a%20time%2C%20Ray%20Dalio%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Bridgewater%20Associates%2C%20the%20biggest%20hedge%20fund%20in%20the%20world%2C%20would%20tell%20anyone%20%E2%80%94%20global%20politicians%2C%20investors%2C%20anyone%20who%20read%20one%20of%20his%20many%20books%20or%20blog%20posts%20%E2%80%94%20about%20China's%20bright%20future.%20Now%20he's%20telling%20everyone%20he's%20minimizing%20his%20exposure%20to%20the%20country%20and%20that%20there%20will%20be%20no%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2024-09-18%2Fdalio-sees-real-issues-in-china-keeps-small-exposure%3Futm_source%3Dwebsite%26utm_medium%3Dshare%26utm_campaign%3Dtwitter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bbeautiful%20deleveraging%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20China.%20This%20is%20the%20last%20thing%20Beijing%20needs%20seeping%20into%20the%20minds%20of%20US%20policymakers.%20One%20former%20East%20Asia%20State%20Department%20official%20told%20me%20China%20is%20sending%20CCP%20delegations%20to%20DC%20like%20mad%2C%20but%20no%20one%20will%20meet%20with%20them.%20Without%20allies%2C%20Washington%20is%20a%20lonely%20(or%20hostile)%20place%20for%20foreign%20governments%2C%20especially%20when%20those%20foreign%20governments%20have%20crafted%20an%20economic%20strategy%20that%20can%20potentially%20disadvantage%20our%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20heading%20into%20another%20trade%20war%20no%20matter%20who%20is%20president%2C%26quot%3B%20Miller%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BThe%20economic%20model%20Xi%20wants%20is%20not%20compatible%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20mindset%20is%20to%20look%20at%20it%20from%20a%20national%20security%20perspective%20rather%20than%20an%20economic%20perspective.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20distinctions%20between%20what%20a%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20and%20a%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20would%20mean%20for%20that%20trade%20war%2C%20though.%20Harris'%20camp%20would%20pursue%20a%20more%20incremental%20strategy%2C%20targeted%20toward%20protecting%20industries%20tied%20to%20tech%20and%20national%20security%2C%20and%20more%20in%20concert%20with%20our%20allies%20%E2%80%94%20a%20group%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchinamediaproject.org%2Fthe_ccp_dictionary%2Fus-west%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECCP%20has%20begun%20pejoratively%20calling%20%26quot%3BUS-West.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20It's%20an%20attempt%20to%20paint%20the%20US%20as%20dragging%20its%20allies%20along%20with%20our%20trade%20policies%20kicking%20and%20screaming.%20Trump%20would%20create%20more%20chaos%20and%20disunity%20between%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20which%20serves%20Beijing%20in%20the%20trade%20wars.%20However%2C%20he'll%20likely%20surround%20himself%20with%20China%20advisors%20who%20are%20much%20more%20aggressive%20and%20have%20a%20wider%20array%20of%20opinions%20on%20how%20to%20attack%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20a%20bull%20in%20a%20china%20shop%20strategy%2C%20if%20you%20will.%20For%20Beijing%2C%20the%20problem%20is%20that%20this%20fractious%20group%20will%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20trip%20over%20its%20red%20line%3A%20Taiwan%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Trump%20lacks%20the%20attention%20span%20and%20temperament%20to%20stop%20them.%20The%20CCP%20has%20a%20plan%20for%20how%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20trade%20war%2C%20a%20kinetic%20war%20over%20Taiwan%20is%20much%20more%20worrisome%20for%20them%20and%20the%20entire%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite%20House%20aside%2C%20Beijing%20has%20a%20blind%20spot%20here.%20The%20former%20State%20Department%20official%20told%20me%20that%20CCP%20officials%20don't%20fully%20understand%20the%20amount%20of%20power%20Congress%20wields.%20And%20Congress%20has%20become%20stridently%20anti-China.%20Even%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F09%2F13%2Fhouse-republicans-china-wall-street-00179056%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublicans%20on%20the%20House%20Financial%20Services%20Committee%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20once%20willing%20to%20let%20Wall%20Street%20invest%20freely%20in%20the%20Chinese%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20cannot%20agree%20about%20how%20stringent%20to%20make%20limitations%20on%20investing%20there.%20Some%20want%20to%20go%20hard%3B%20others%20want%20to%20go%20harder.%20The%20bipartisan%20House%20Select%20Committee%20on%20China%20has%20no%20problem%20firing%20warning%20shots%20at%20some%20of%20China's%20last%20corporate%20allies%2C%20the%20semiconductor%20companies.%20China's%20own%20attempts%20to%20develop%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-xi-jiinping-future-tech-global-economy-semiconductors-military-failing-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edomestic-chip%20supply%20chain%3C%2Fa%3E%20still%20lag%20behind%20the%20state%20of%20the%20art%2C%20so%20it%20needs%20US%20companies%20like%20Broadcom%20and%20Nvidia.%20Those%20companies%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20love%20the%20billions%20they%20make%20in%20China.%20But%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fcommitteeonccp%2Fstatus%2F1835753593367912600%3Futm_source%3Dsubstack%26utm_medium%3Demail%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseries%20of%20tweets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Select%20Committee%20urged%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20ignore%20semiconductor%20lobbyists%20working%20in%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20urge%20the%20Biden%20Administration%20to%20maintain%20the%20strong%20export%20controls%20put%20in%20place%20in%20October%202022%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%20%26quot%3BWeakening%20these%20measures%20would%20raise%20serious%20concerns%20about%20safeguarding%20U.S.%20technological%20leadership%20and%20our%20national%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20these%20%5Bsemiconductor%5D%20CEOs%20believe%20that%20current%20US%20export%20control%20policy%20is%20bad%20for%20the%20US%20economy%20and%20our%20national%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3Bthen%20they%20must%20make%20that%20case%20publicly%2C%20perhaps%20before%20a%20congressional%20committee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiller%20told%20me%20that%20a%20tech%20decoupling%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20isn't%20a%20problem%20for%20Congress%20anymore%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20a%20goal.%20%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20this%20is%20talking%20to%20US%20companies%20who%20have%20a%20big%20share%20in%20China%20and%20are%20saying%2C%20'You%20can't%20do%20this%20to%20us%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWell%2C%20guess%20what%3F%20There%20are%20tradeoffs.%20Right%20now%2C%20we're%20not%20paying%20a%20high%20enough%20price%20for%20the%20right%20policy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20price%20of%20this%20shift%20cannot%20be%20quantified%20in%20corporate%20profits.%20It%20cannot%20be%20quantified%20in%20dollars%20at%20all.%20Cordell%20Hull%2C%20the%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20from%201933%20to%201944%20and%20recipient%20of%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-helping-american-farmers-could-start-trade-war-2018-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonce%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BUnhampered%20trade%20dovetailed%20with%20peace%3B%20high%20tariffs%2C%20trade%20barriers%2C%20and%20unfair%20competition%20with%20war.%26quot%3B%20Putting%20national%20security%2C%20rather%20than%20economic%20cooperation%2C%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20US-China%20relationship%20centers%20it%20in%20a%20space%20where%20the%20two%20