20she%20has%20given%20just%20little%20more%20than%20half%20a%20dozen%20press%20interviews%2C%20and%20things%20haven't%20been%20much%20different%20for%20Walz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20experts%20say%20it's%20a%20risky%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20clear%20exactly%20why%20Harris%20and%20Walz%20have%20been%20so%20press-shy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20benefits%20to%20the%20campaign's%20approach.%20Both%20Harris%20and%20Walz%20are%20able%20to%20avoid%20the%20gaffes%20and%20unscripted%20missteps%20that%20plagued%20both%20Biden's%202024%20campaign%20and%20Harris'%20own%202020%20presidential%20campaign.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-talking-about-harris-appearance-ignores-advice-analysis-dnc-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjd-vance-defended-his-childless-cat-ladies-comment-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJD%20Vance's%3C%2Fa%3E%20many%20press%20interviews%20have%20sparked%20negative%20news%20cycles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20risks%20may%20be%20greater%20than%20any%20rewards.%20Political%20scientists%20warn%20that%20this%20strategy%20could%20hurt%20their%20campaign%20if%20it%20hasn't%20already%2C%20particularly%20at%20a%20time%20when%20many%20voters%20say%20they%20don't%20know%20enough%20about%20the%20candidates%20or%20their%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELonna%20Atkeson%2C%20a%20political%20science%20professor%20at%20Florida%20State%20University%20and%20director%20of%20nonpartisan%20think%20tank%20LeRoy%20Collins%20Institute%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Harris'%20limited%20interactions%20with%20the%20press%20risk%20sowing%20distrust%20among%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20poor%20strategy%20because%20it%20leaves%20open%20a%20lot%20of%20suspicions%2C%26quot%3B%20Atkeson%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20those%20suspicions%20raise%20questions%20for%20voters%2C%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhy%20don't%20you%20want%20to%20tell%20us%20about%20yourself%3F%20Are%20you%20not%20capable%20of%20doing%20that%3F%20Why%20is%20it%20that%20you%20can't%20communicate%20and%20talk%20to%20other%20people%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20their%20leaders%2C%26quot%3B%20Atkeson%20added.%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20leaders%20who%20are%20going%20to%20raise%20us%20up%2C%20and%20it%20raises%20questions%20about%20her%20ability%20to%20raise%20us%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAtkeson%20also%20gave%20the%20analogy%20that%20the%20effect%20of%20Harris'%20media%20strategy%20on%20voters%20is%20like%20what%20happens%20when%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20first%20begins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20happens%20when%20you%20first%20meet%20someone%20and%20you're%20excited%20about%20them%20is%20you%20project%20all%20of%20this%20stuff%20on%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Atkeson%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20she%20first%20came%20onto%20the%20stage%2C%20she%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20passes%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20projection.%20The%20projection%20is%2C%20'okay%2C%20we've%20got%20this%20exciting%20younger%20candidate%20meets%20all%20these%20criteria%2C'%20and%20so%20there's%20sort%20of%20this%20love%20affair%20going%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20what's%20supposed%20to%20happen%20next%2C%20Atkeson%20added%2C%20is%20you%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20person%20and%20the%20projection%20fades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20if%20you%20were%20in%20a%20love%20affair%20and%20your%20partner%20refuses%20to%20answer%20questions%20or%20talk%20to%20you%20about%20things%2C%20well%2C%20that%20would%20really%20start%20to%20change%20your%20mind%20about%20how%20you%20feel%20about%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Atkeson%20explained.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20it's%20like%2C%20'well%2C%20gee%2C%20they're%20awfully%20secret.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20strategy%20can%20only%20work%20so%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20Atkeson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20has%20been%20sticking%20to%20more%20structured%20%E2%80%94%20and%20less%20traditional%20%E2%80%94%20media%20appearances%2C%20like%20a%20livestream%20event%20with%20Oprah%20Winfrey%20on%20Thursday%20evening.%20Winfrey%20has%20endorsed%20Harris%20for%20president%20and%20the%20questions%20she%20faced%20were%20hardly%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2Fu9-cjwpthz4%3Fsi%3DXNzcsIdpQKLx3Amb%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWIRED%20published%20a%20video%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20which%20Harris%20answered%20the%20web's%20most%20searched%20questions%20about%20her%2C%20like%20where%20she's%20from%2C%20what%20her%20childhood%20was%20like%2C%20what%20she%20stands%20for%2C%20etc.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20magazine's%20popular%20video%20series%20has%20mostly%20been%20used%20by%20celebrities%20during%20press%20junkets%20%E2%80%94%20not%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EW.%20Joseph%20Campbell%2C%20a%20communications%20professor%20emeritus%20at%20American%20University%20who%20specializes%20in%20presidential%20polling%20and%20political%20media%2C%20echoed%20Atkeson's%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSpeaking%20in%20platitudes%20and%20avoiding%20the%20press%20is%20not%20necessarily%20a%20winning%20strategy%2C%26quot%3B%20Campbell%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20should%20be%20doing%20more%20interviews.%20They%20should%20do%20news%20conferences.%20This%20is%20part%20and%20parcel%20of%20a%20presidential%20election%20campaign.%20And%20to%20avoid%20doing%20them%20raises%20questions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECampbell%20said%20polling%20data%20is%20clear%20that%20many%20Americans%20say%20they%20want%20to%20know%20more%20about%20Harris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris'%20lack%20of%20press%20interaction%2C%20particularly%20with%20unfriendly%20outlets%20like%20Fox%20News%20or%20others%2C%20is%20also%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20her%20opponent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTrump%20seems%20inclined%20to%20meet%20with%20just%20about%20anybody%2C%20and%20he%20has%20met%20with%20reporters%20on%20a%20frequent%20basis%20over%20his%20many%20years%20of%20trying%20to%20run%20and%20then%20winning%20the%20presidency%2C%26quot%3B%20Campbell%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20was%20pretty%20accessible%20during%20his%20years%20in%20office%2C%20as%20well%20as%20before%20and%20after%20and%20during%20this%20campaign%20as%20well.%20So%20the%20contrast%20could%20be%20something%20that%20doesn't%20look%20good%20optically%20for%20the%20Harris%20campaign.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20some%20of%20Harris'%20fellow%20Democrats%20are%20starting%20to%20worry%20about%20her%20minimal%20press%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore.%20More.%20More%2C%26quot%3B%20Van%20Jones%2C%20a%20Democratic%20commentator%20and%20former%20Obama%20administration%20official%2C%20said%20this%20week%20on%20CNN.%20%26quot%3BThe%20polls%20show%20the%20more%20you%20see%20Kamala%2C%20the%20more%20you%20like%20Kamala.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Democratic%20strategists%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthehill.com%2Fhomenews%2Fcampaign%2F4887335-kamala-harris-low-key-media%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20Hill%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20want%20to%20see%20Harris%20ramping%20up%20her%20media%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Harris%20campaign%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F09%2F17%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Fkamala-harris-media-strategy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20more%20press%20interviews%20are%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20questions%20remains%3A%20will%20it%20be%20too%20little%2C%20too%20late%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharris-walz-limited-media-presence-interviews-risky-strategy-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3