C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Driver%20works%20at%20a%20private%20school%2C%20classroom%20funding%20can%20be%20limited%20since%20it%20comes%20from%20student%20tuition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20my%20school%20is%20doing%20the%20best%20they%20can%20with%20what%20they%20have%20to%20help%20us%20with%20our%20classroom%20supplies%2C%26quot%3B%20Driver%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20nice%20if%20they%20could%20do%20more%2C%20but%20that%20always%20depends%20on%20the%20number%20of%20students%20we%20have%20enrolled.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20private%20and%20charter%20school%20educators%20who%20spend%20their%20money.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnces.ed.gov%2Fsurveys%2Fntps%2Festable%2Ftable%2Fntps%2Fntps2021_6801_t12ns%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESurvey%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20previous%20years%20show%20teachers%20in%20%26quot%3Btraditional%26quot%3B%20public%20schools%20have%20to%20spend%20out%20of%20pocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYelena%20Khazan%2C%20a%20first-grade%20teacher%20at%20a%20public%20school%20in%20Florida%20serving%20some%20low-income%20families%2C%20is%20excited%20about%20what's%20to%20come%20during%20her%20first%20year%20as%20a%20full-time%20teacher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20organized%20a%20GoFundMe%20fundraiser%20to%20help%20buy%20items%20for%20her%20classroom.%20%24845%20of%20her%20%242%2C000%20goal%20had%20been%20raised.%20Khazan%20said%20she%20spent%20some%20of%20her%20own%20savings%20on%20top%20of%20the%20money%20from%20the%20fundraiser.%20Documentation%20shared%20with%20Business%20Insider%20showed%20she%20had%20spent%20well%20over%20%242%2C000%20for%20supplies%20and%20decorations%20on%20Amazon%20and%20through%20other%20sites.%20She%20also%20bought%20items%20at%20local%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKhazan%20said%20in%20addition%20to%20students%20bringing%20in%20items%20on%20their%20school%20supply%20lists%2C%20some%20parents%20have%20offered%20even%20more%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20spent%20money%20on%20things%20for%20her%20classroom%20because%20she%20wanted%20to%20provide%20her%20students%20with%20what%20they%20would%20need%20to%20be%20successful%20and%20because%20she%20wanted%20to%20create%20a%20comfortable%20environment%2C%20given%20how%20much%20time%20she%20and%20her%20students%20would%20be%20in%20the%20classroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20want%20them%20to%20feel%20like%20they%20can%20express%20themselves%2C%20they%20feel%20emotionally%20safe%2C%20and%20I%20want%20it%20to%20be%20a%20welcoming%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Khazan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Yelena%20Khazan's%20classroom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66e83dd6bf0250c21493a226%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYelena%20Khazan%20bought%20books%2C%20storage%2C%20and%20flexible%20seating%20items.%3Cp%3EYelena%20Khazan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMajors%20said%20that%20schools%20in%20lower-income%20communities%20%26quot%3Boften%20are%20under-resourced%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btheir%20families%20may%20not%20have%20the%20means%20for%20all%20the%20tools%20that%20they%20might%20need%20in%20the%20classroom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMajors%20said%20people%20who%20want%20to%20support%20teachers%2C%20even%20if%20they%20don't%20have%20school-aged%20children%2C%20could%20see%20if%20their%20school%20district%20has%20a%20donation%20fund%20or%20if%20they%20could%20drop%20off%20school%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e771c6ef-a8e9-4a41-9c1f-574dbe4a22fd%5C%22%3EWhat%20the%20three%20teachers%20bought%20for%20their%20classroom%20goals%20and%20needs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDriver%20said%20no%20one%20wants%20to%20go%20into%20a%20boring%20classroom%2C%20and%20she%20bought%20most%20of%20the%20items%20in%20her%20room.%20She%20spent%20over%20%24800%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20Amazon%20purchases%20alone%20this%20summer%20for%20her%20classroom%20and%20school%20sports%20she%20coaches%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20typically%20have%20to%20buy%20things%20that%20sometimes%20the%20kids%20just%20don't%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Driver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20school%20helps%20with%20archery%20supplies%2C%20one%20of%20the%20sports%20she%20coaches%2C%20but%20she%20bought%20some%20items%20for%20flag%20football%20and%20basketball.%20For%20instance%2C%20she%20bought%20basketball%20goggles%2C%20a%20basketball%20rack%2C%20and%20flag%20football%20belts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20items%20Driver%20bought%20this%20summer%20include%20paint%20brushes%2C%20dot%20markers%2C%20a%20rug%2C%20and%20musical%20instruments.%20She%20said%20she%20also%20bought%20a%20poster%20that%20her%20students%20can%20press%20to%20learn%20about%20the%20sounds%20of%20the%20alphabet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20trying%20to%20keep%20them%20away%20from%20the%20iPads%2C%20but%20I%20still%20want%20them%20to%20be%20able%20to%20learn%20because%20all%20of%20them%20are%20so%20used%20to%20that%20instant%20gratification%20that%20I%20was%20looking%20for%20something%20else%20to%20be%20able%20to%20give%20them%20that%20besides%20an%20iPad%20or%20a%20tablet%2C%26quot%3B%20Driver%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKhazan%20bought%20books%2C%20magnetic%20tiles%2C%20storage%20and%20organizational%20items%2C%20and%20worksheets%2C%20among%20other%20things.%20Flexible%20seating%20items%20were%20also%20a%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20the%20interview%2C%20Khazan%20expected%20arts%20and%20crafts%2C%20STEM%20materials%2C%20and%20printing%20fees%20to%20be%20the%20main%20expenses%20for%20the%20classroom%20moving%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohnson%20thinks%20students%20will%20be%20interested%20in%20learning%20and%20be%20more%20likely%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her%20items%20the%20more%20%26quot%3Baesthetically%20pleasing%26quot%3B%20her%20classroom%20is.%20She%20has%20posters%20hung%20up%2C%20lamps%2C%20and%20different%20seating%20for%20students%20to%20use%20in%20addition%2